Method of Communication: Verbal 

Results:  Researcher Karen ██████ approached the branch on which SCP-1468-29 was carving the beginning of Chapter 3 of I Am Legend, by Richard Matheson, and said  SCP-1468-29 displayed no changes in behavior. Researcher Karen ██████ repeated the greeting in Spanish, French, German, Russian, Japanese, and Mandarin Chinese, none of which elicited a response from SCP-1468-29.

Attempt #2 

Method of Communication: Written 

Results:  Researcher Karen ██████ displayed a document with  written in twenty-nine different dialects to SCP-1468-29. SCP-1468-29 observed pausing briefly in its carving to look at the document for approximately ten seconds before returning to work.

Attempt #3 

Method of Communication: Carving 

Results:  Researcher Karen ██████ displayed a piece of wood with  into its transcription of I Am Legend.

Attempt #4 

Method of Communication: Carving 

Results:  Using several blocks of wood with questions carved into them, Researcher Karen ██████ conducted a rough interview of SCP-1468-29. Enclosed are the results, with SCP-1468-29's carving of I Am Legend excluded.





